To test, run the "ti sdk" command to determine the default Titanium SDK install location. For Mac OS X, the default install location is "~/Library/Application Support/Titanium".

Next, run:

{code}
sudo chown root:admin ~/Library/Application\ Support/Titanium
{code}

Then run "titanium sdk install --branch master" to try to download the latest SDK. The install will fail and the SDK is not downloaded.

To restore your folder permissions, run:

{code}
sudo chown YOUR_USER_NAME:staff ~/Library/Application\ Support/Titanium
{code}
